# Angular Project

This is an Angular project.

## Prerequisites

To run this project locally, you need the following installed on your machine:

- [Node.js](https://nodejs.org/)
- [npm](https://www.npmjs.com/)
- [Angular CLI](https://angular.io/cli)
- [Cypress](https://www.cypress.io/) (installed via npm)

## Getting Started

1. Install Dependencies
Navigate into the project directory and install the required dependencies:

npm install

2. Run the Development Server
To run the application in development mode, use the Angular CLI command:

ng serve

The app will be available at http://localhost:4200/

3. Generate UI Testing scripts
Using the extension to generate UI Testing script for Cypress in Javascript by uploading 6 files:
- app.component.ts
- app.component.html
- user-form.component.ts
- user-form.component.html
- user-list.component.ts
- user-list.component.html

Name the generated file as test.cy.js and put the file in cypress/e2e

4. Start testing

Set cypress.config.ts
    baseUrl: 'http://localhost:4200'

Open Cypress UI and start testing UI of the app on Chrome.

npx cypress open
